The paper deals with communication over a channel with a jamming adversary, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The adversary is subject to quadratic constraints, which suggests a connection to cryptography (cs.CR) or optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses numerical simulations, which could fall under the category of scientific computing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves characterizing the channel capacity, which could be related to data structures (cs.DS) or algorithms (cs.AL).
